  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Joan Segovia</h1>
      <h2>Front-end Developer, from Argentina.</h2>
    </header>

    <section id="about">
      <h3>About Me</h3>
      <p>
        In 2016, I started diving headfirst into the world of web development.
        Armed with pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, I began my exploration of
        what coding offered. Similar to falling down a rabbit hole, I quickly
        became captivated by the potential and creativity that coding and web
        development provided.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since then, I've been honing my skills and learning everything I could.
        From building websites with a CMS to the development of mobile apps,
        I've gained invaluable experience and a deep passion for crafting
        exceptional digital experiences.
      </p>
      <p>
        As of right now, I'm seeking new opportunities to apply my knowledge,
        open to full-time positions or freelance gigs, ready to contribute. As a
        web developer, I leverage my expertise in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and a
        range of modern frameworks to create responsive, user-friendly, and
        visually appealing websites.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I'm not immersed in the IDE or reading docs, I enjoy drinking <a
          href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mate_(drink)">mate</a
        >
        with <a
          href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croissant#Argentina_and_Uruguay"
          >medialunas</a
        >, and strategizing my way to victory in Hearts of Iron 4, trying to
        conquer the world. I also love hitting the gym to stay active, riding my
        bike, and watching football, my favorite sport.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-experience">
      <h3>Work Experience</h3>
      <h4>IbisDev</h4>
      <p>June 2022 - Feb 2023</p>
      <p>
        At <a href="https://ibisdev.tech">IbisDev</a>, I developed and mantained
        front-end applications using JavaScript, Next.js, and TypeScript. I
        worked with web scraping, UI design, and collaborating with project
        managers. Skilled in code reviews and remote work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="projects">
      <h3>Projects</h3>
      <p>Coming soon!</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        Do you want to hire me for a project, an idea, or just talk to me? You
        can do it by emailing me at [EMAIL ADDRESS]
      </p>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <p>
        Website coded in VS Code, with Astro and deployed in Vercel. Fonts are
        Geologica and Inter and colors are #16161a, #fffffe, #94a1c4, and
        #7f5af0.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
